grubber
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:The usual NZ generic name for Eng. `mattock, adze' for rooting up weeds, plants etc. Of two main kinds: (a) one blade in the form of a heavy hoe or adze (the handle is, of course, the short pick-handle) and the other blade in the form of an axe; (b) with one hoe-like or adze-like blade with nothing on the back end; mattock (US? grub-hoe)


